preoccupations of the psychoanalytic approach, she reveals how a religious and ethical relation to the "ordeal" of madness might actually allow for spiritual transformation.   This sophisticated and evocative work illuminates new dimensions of psychoanalysis and the ethical imagination while also sensitively examining the collective psychic strife that so many communities endure today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aIslam and psychoanalysiszMorocco. 0aIslamzMoroccoxCustoms and practices. 0aMental healthxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aMental illnessxAlternative treatmentzMorocco. 0aPastoral psychology (Islam) 4aIslam. 4aMorocco. 4adespair. 4amadness. 4apsychoanalysis. 4aspiritual transformation. 4athe soul. 4aunconscious. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226465111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226465111.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles